      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing conducted at minimum two loading rates or environmental conditions to bracket COU; ASTM F1717 protocol followed with documented deviations.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted strictly per ASTM F1717 at a single displacement rate (5 mm/min) and ambient laboratory temperature. Only one test condition was evaluated, limiting the achieved level to 2. This shortfall is acknowledged; the impact on overall credibility is mitigated by the strong agreement between FEA and experiment across both laboratories and the sub-yield nature of the loading regime."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
