      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions demonstrably equivalent to physical test fixture constraints; applied loads and displacements matched to within measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 fixture geometry digitized and incorporated into the FEA model. Applied displacement boundary condition matched to crosshead displacement corrected for machine compliance (measured separately). Grip constraint representations verified against fixture drawings. Equivalency confirmed through pre-test simulation of the fixture alone."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all primary QoIs; percent difference < 10% for each QoI.",
      "rationale": "All three primary QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) satisfy both acceptance criteria. E/uval values of 0.87, 1.31, and 1.54 are all below 1.96. Percent differences of 4.2%, 6.8%, and 7.1% are all below 10%. The validation metric accounts for experimental variability across both laboratories and model parameter uncertainty."
    },
