      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly correspond to regulatory submission endpoints; clinical relevance of each QoI documented in the analysis plan.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in the ASTM F1717 standard and are the metrics cited in 510(k) submissions for pedicle screw systems. Each QoI is directly linked to a failure mode of clinical consequence (fatigue initiation, permanent deformation, gross failure) in the analysis plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
