      "rationale": "The validation scenario replicates the COU geometry (7.5 mm non-cannulated screw, standard rod diameter) and loading modality (compression-bending per F1717) exactly. The validation constructs are drawn from the same production lot as those intended for the COU submission. The sole difference — use of UHMWPE vertebral body surrogates rather than cadaveric bone — is consistent with the ASTM standard and is common practice for regulatory submissions."
