    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility is assessed as sufficient to support regulatory use. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is judged acceptable given the strong quantitative agreement across all three QoIs at both laboratories, the sub-yield nature of the loading regime, and the direct correspondence between the validation scenario and the COU. The FEA modeling framework is accepted for predicting ASTM F1717 compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
